Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry; season with @Garlic Powder{1%tsp}, @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}.

Drizzle @Cooking Oil{1%tsp} in a hot #large pan{}. Cook chicken until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

> TIP: If chicken is browning too quickly, reduce heat to medium and cover pan with lid.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce.

Dice @Potatoes{12%ounce} into 1-inch pieces (peel if desired).

In a #large microwave-safe bowl{}, season potatoes with salt and pepper. Add @Butter{2%tablespoon} to bowl and cover with #plastic wrap{}.

Microwave until potatoes are tender and steaming, ~{6-7%minutes}. Remove plastic wrap and stir to combine.

> TIP: If your potatoes need more time to cook, cover bowl with plastic wrap again and microwave in 1-minute intervals.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}(thinly sliced) greens (save whites for another use).

> TIP: While potatoes and chicken cook, feel free to toss the salad in the salad assembly step!

In pan used for chicken, off heat, whisk together @Cream Sauce Base{4%ounce}, @White Cheddar Cheese{1%cup}, scallion greens, and a splash of water until thoroughly combined and smooth, ~{30-60%seconds}.

> TIP: If the cheese isn't melting, return pan to low heat.

In a #second large bowl{}, combine @Mixed Greens{4%ounce}, @Sunflower Seeds{1/2%ounce}, and @Dried Cherries{1%ounce} with @Greek Vinaigrette{3%ounce}.

Drizzle chicken and potatoes with as much cheddar sauce as you like. Serve with salad on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°